{"word":"ἀλόη","slug":"ἀλόη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀλόη, ης, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Skt.\">Skt.</a> via <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Heb.\">Heb.</a>] an aromatic substance apparently derived from what is known as ‘eaglewood’, syntactically <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ sg.\">sg.</a> but usually rendered <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pl.\">pl.</a> <b><i>aloes</i> <a href='B:500 19:39'>J 19:39</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἄλογος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἁλυκός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}